About
-----

bristolgui is a graphical user interface for the bristol 
synthesizer emulation (http://bristol.sourceforge.net, 
author: Nick Copeland). Written in ANSI-C, using the GTK. 
bristolgui is Free Software, see the "License" section.

bristolgui runs only on Linux and BSD systems.
Since there is no equivalent to JACK or ALSA on MS Windows based 
operating systems, porting it would make no sense at all.

